raw_data.name: The Traveling Sip Cafe
raw_data.full_address: 132 N Gaston St, Dallas, NC 28034, United States
raw_data.description: Coffee shop that's best know for canning our iced lattes! We started with a coffee trailer and now we have expanded into a permeant location. Thank you for being a friend :)

reviews_data.review_text: This place is the best coffee shop around! The staff, the coffee, the atmosphere and overall the theme of the shop!!  It’s a must if you’re in the area!!! You will not be disappointed!!

The cafe is super cute and the service was great, but overall it is not worth the price or the hype. I bought an iced decaf americano with half and half and a pump of caramel flavoring and it tasted like diluted coffee. No flavor at all. I understand this isn’t the type of drinks that they usually serve so I also bought a matcha latte with a strawberry cold foam for my daughter. The taste of that one wasn’t much better. It tasted like diluted strawberry milk and had no matcha taste at all. With tip, I paid over $15 for two drinks that had no flavor profile and those weren’t even their most expensive drinks. With that being said, it could have been a fluke, but I’m not willing to try it again. I’ll stick to Waterbean or some of the other local shops in the area.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Michelle,
Owner here of The Traveling Sip. Thanks for stopping by and for taking the time to share your feedback. We’re glad to hear you enjoyed the space and service — that’s something we take great pride in.

As for the drinks, we’re sorry they didn’t meet your expectations. Based on what you ordered — an iced decaf americano with half & half and a pump of caramel — the lighter, more diluted taste you experienced is actually typical for that style, especially with decaf and added dairy, which naturally softens the flavor. - The matcha latte with strawberry cold foam also leans toward a more subtle, creamy profile rather than something very bold or sweet.

That said, taste is personal, and your feedback is valuable. If you ever choose to give us another try, we'd love to recommend something more in line with your preferences — something bolder or more robust in flavor.


We appreciate your visit!

reviews_data.review_text: I am so displeased, I traveled about 45 mins for it to be closed  - no communication on any pages IG and facebook are no longer available i am just so confused because google said its open ): i was so excited to try
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Nia,
Owner here of The Traveling Sip, I am so sorry we were closed when you came by the cafe this past week, it was a weird week for us. Our IG page got banned for more than 48hours and then the town of Dallas had a water line that broke which left the whole town with no water. We posted this on our Facebook page about the water line, hoping to get the word out that we had to close unexpectedly, however it was very upsetting for us not being able to inform our IG friends as well. Again I am so sorry for the inconvenience this caused you. If you get a chance to come by again please reach out to us and we will make it right.

reviews_data.review_text: We had the Betty White and the Pink Sip! Both were SO GOOD! Will definitely be coming back to try the rest. Friendly barista and relaxing environment.
The cutest shop! Coffee is great!
Literally the cutest coffee spot with the best coffee! Plus, thanks to their can top drinks I can buy multiple drinks and easily transport without fear of spilling! Genius!

This is the absolute BEST coffee shop in town! Starbucks ain’t got nothing on them! It is so stinking cute! The cans the coffee comes in are super cute too! They ever have pink heart shaped straws! Hands down 100 out of 10!!
Very cute coffee shop, I ordered a caramel frappe - delicious!! ✨The shop went viral online so there was a line out the door. But those ladies held it down & everything went smoothly! ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️☕️

I visited The Traveling Sip today and this charming, unique boutique coffee shoppe in the heart of downtown Dallas is delightful. I enjoyed a Sarcastic Dorothy-a strawberry cheesecake themed espresso latte. The drinks come in thick, plastic can with tops that open like a soda can.

I high recommend this shoppe.
Sweet spot with great coffee, beautiful scenery, and friendly staff! Love it
Love love love their coffees and the fact that they come in sealed cans and are good for 5 days
Such a cute little friendly place! I loved it!
Soooo good very good service they are very nice try now!!!
I tried this new coffee shop this morning.  The decor is so cute and drink is phenomenal. I tried the caramel frappe. 😍 Also.. look at that cute resuable heart straw. ❤️
Absolutely beautiful coffee shop with such friendly staff and great drinks!
Beautiful place and inviting.  Staff were friendly and engaging even though they were super busy opening day.
I have been drinking the traveling sip since the beginning. The coffee is always amazing and the staff is the sweetest. So happy for the store front now!
